<h1 >
    THE FROG
</h1>
<P>The Chorus of Frogs by Aunt Effie<br>
<strong>Frogs</strong> by Sir Charles George Douglas Roberts:<br>
Upon the Frog by John Bunyan<br>
<strong style="color:red"><em>The Tree Toad</em></strong> by John Brainard<br>
The Song of the Toad by John Burroughs<br>
The Tree-Frog Pedigree by John B. Tabb
    
</P>
<h2>

    SUNGURA MJANJA
</h2>
<img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/cute/EnemyBug.png">
<p>
   Hadithi inayokuja, ni ya sungura sikia<br>
hadithi uliyongoja leo ninakuletea<br>
Alitoka siku moja njaa aliposikia<br>
njaa aliposikia sungura nakuambia<br>

Siku hiyo akaenda porini kutembelea<br>
akayaona matunda mtini yameenea<br>

sungura akayapenda mtini akasogea<br>
Mtini akasogea sungura nakuambia<br>

sungura karuka ruka lakini hakufikia<br>
matunda hakuyashika mikononi hakutia<br>
hakika alisumbuka nguvuze zikapungua<br>
nguvuze zikapungua sungura namwambia<br>


</p>
<h3>
    SWEET BANANA
</h3>
